item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: vaibhavwebdev23
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:

Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)

...or something like this:

The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.

As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: Privacy Policy
item.dc:creator: vaibhavwebdev23
item.content:encoded:
Who we are

Suggested text: Our website address is: http:.

Comments

Suggested text: When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor’s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.

An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.

Media

Suggested text: If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.

Cookies

Suggested text: If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.

If you visit our login page, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.

When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select "Remember Me", your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.

If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.

Embedded content from other websites

Suggested text: Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.

These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.

Who we share your data with

Suggested text: If you request a password reset, your IP address will be included in the reset email.

How long we retain your data

Suggested text: If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.

For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.

What rights you have over your data

Suggested text: If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.

Where we send your data

Suggested text: Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.

item.title: Homepage
item.dc:creator: vaibhavwebdev23
item.content:encoded:
Key Features of HCAS

Real Time Face Detection with Tracking

Our system will make use of a pre-installed camera which will be mounted on a servo controlled platform that will allow it to track people in the health center, keep count of the number of people and also have an optional Face Recognition System inbuilt.

Automated Appointer & Counter

We will be using RFID Scanners & Camera to check the number of people in waiting room and schedule their instant appointment with the doctor as they walk into the health center. All they need to do is scan their ID card / Show their face to the camera

Real Time Conversation Transcribing

We plan to include a consent-based automated system that can listen and transcribe the entire conversation between the doctor and the patient and add it to the meeting logs in the database for reference.

Remote Reminder and Summary System

We will be implementing the use of Web Scraping and Database Management System with intelligent text analysis systems which will be able to provide reminders to the patients regarding their medicine times and monthly health center visit summary.

For small Health Centers

0 Patients

We can handle as many Patients as your Healthcare Corporation wants us to handle.

For Big Health Centers

0 Patients https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XHOmBV4js_E

Want to know how we implement our System ?

This one hour video will give you a better understanding of our work and this video also covers all the domains that our project is based upon.

Click here

Programming Languages that we rely on

Python Language used in HCAS 95% Embedded C Language used in HCAS 10% Html Language used in HCAS 15%

Softwares we use in HCAS

Spyder python

Spyder is an IDE aimed at mainly scientific researchers, data analysts, or those involved in scientific package creation. Spyders developers have designed it to be the ideal tool for developing Python applications, and Spyder itself has been created using Python.

Jupyter python

JupyterLab is a web-based interactive development environment for Jupyter notebooks, code, and data. JupyterLab is flexible: configure and arrange the user interface to support a wide range of workflows in data science, scientific computing, and machine learning. It write plugins that add new components and integrate with existing ones.

TinkerCad

Tinkercad is an online collection of software tools from Autodesk that enable complete beginners to create 3D models. This CAD software is based on constructive solid geometry (CSG), which allows users to create complex models by combining simpler objects together.

Services already available at our STORE

Click here to get to the STORE

Image Classification

Humans are very good at categorizing scenes based on the semantic representation and object affinity, but we know very little about the processing and encoding of natural scene categories in the human brain. The same cant be said about the machines, The problem arises when we are required to determine a suitable classification system, selection of training samples, image preprocessing, feature extraction, etc. Image classification is the process of predicting a specific class, or label, for something that is defined by a set of data points. Image classification is a subset of the classification problem.

Click here to know more

item.content:encoded:
Our New approach will revolutionize the Patient Management at Hospitals

OUR AIM

The main issue we are trying to counter is the inefficiency caused to only using human factor in highly repetitive tasks. We will be solving this by including automation along with a host of other features. We aim to automate every feature that is possible to be automated and does not require direct human support. So, at the end of our Project we are aiming to manage the different tasks of health Centre efficiently and now that we know that the tasks like Database management is handled automatically there is a very little or no window for errors. It will save a lot of time of the Human Resource and they can focus on more urgent and important tasks.

Who we are ?

We are a bunch of Engineering Students who started with the idea to Automate the Patient Management at their College's Health Center. As we succeeded with our idea. We now aim to implement our model on Bigger Hospitals and larger Health Centers.

item.content:encoded:
Technologies that we offer

Machine Learning

Deep Learning

Arduino programming

RFID Scanner and Chips

Optical character Recognition

Speech Recognition

OOPs Concept

Facial Recognition

The Camera will be able to track people using dedicated software and Arduino setup with dual servo motors. The system will be able to identify people on the basis of face recognition and will be intelligent enough to decide if the person is wearing a face-mask or not and analyse for face detection based on that conclusion. Not just that, the software will be able to count the number of people in the waiting room in real time, track for any unusual activity for security among other enhancements. Apart from that, we will also be able to respond to a patient query about the number of people in waiting area, number of appointments etc. to help them make their plan to visit the center. Automated Appointer & Counter

We will also have the RFID scanner which will also double as a counter to provide the main analysis for the person entering the waiting area and the doctors cabin by scanning their ID card as they go into the respective areas and keeping count of the number of people waiting.The scanner on the doctors cabin door will be the one to trigger the auto opening of the patient database as they enter the cabin. This system will improve both safety and efficiency of the center as a while. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Automatic Patient Record Opener

Our Algorithm will log the in time, out time, appointment time, prescriptions and diagnosis and optionally also save the transcribed conversation into the database for the patient. Not only this, the system will also be capable of sending alerts to the patient to remind them to take their medicines and also allow for remote appointment scheduling among other features.Apart from that, as soon as the patient walks into the doctors cabin, the system will automatically open the patients database in front of the doctor to view and edit as need be. This will save the time needed to search for and open the patient database as he/she enters the cabin and present their entire saved history for better diagnosis.Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Remote Reminder and Summary System

We will be using speech recognition software based on patient and doctor consent to record and transcribe the entire conversation that happens in the cabin using microphones. This information will then be used to analyse and check if the correct prescribed medicines are in-fact given to the patient and a mistake is not made in that.This will also help improve the medicine taking reminder system by analysing the finer text to confirm the times for reminders.Not just that, this will also help the doctors to improve their diagnosis as they will have their entire conversation in front of the, removing the scope of forgetting something on either end.Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. RFID Scanner

Every RFID system consists of three components: a scanningantenna, atransceiverand atransponder. When the scanning antenna and transceiver are combined, they are referred to as an RFID reader or interrogator. There are two types of RFID readers -- fixed readers and mobile readers. The RFID reader is a network-connected device that can be portable or permanently attached. It uses radiowaves to transmit signals that activate the tag. Once activated, the tag sends a wave back to the antenna, where it is translated into data.The transponder is in the RFID tag itself. The read range for RFID tags varies based on factors including the type of tag, type of reader, RFID frequency and interference in the surrounding environment or from other RFID tags and readers. item.title: Machine Learning Services
item.dc:creator: vaibhavwebdev23
item.content:encoded: The future scope of our project is vast. Our base idea was that we worked on the design of a software package in such a way that we are able to expand any aspect of it and even modify the same as and when necessary. Careful use of multiple scripts has paved the way for future expansion, addition of more methods in the start, addition of features such as those for security which can range from just keeping a check on the safety condition of the area using sensor arrays all the way to use of Augmented Reality to keep track of each and every person inside the waiting area along with a system setup for behavioural analysis and risk assessment systems in place. As was mentioned above we have worked on the development of the backend of the system and in the near future we can work on the development of a frontend system for our project in the form of a website or an app or even both.

item.title: Video Classification
item.dc:creator: vaibhavwebdev23
item.content:encoded: Our project named Video Classification is based on Deep Learning and we have mainly focused on CNN (Convolution Neural Network) to train and test our project. Through our project we can input or import in video from different sources weather it be online or offline and can classify on basis of the activity happening inside the video. It can be any activity including topics such as
item.excerpt:encoded: As students, we can very well understand the problems that we face in our daily life. We found out that in recent times as the security in every aspect is increasing its becoming very difficult for, we humans to keep a track of all of it. People are recording stuffs to keep a track of the needful things every time, but with time things starts piling up each and every day and it becomes almost impossible of a mere human to keep track of all of it that has happened in due time

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: We thought that what if we can come up with a solution through which a computer or a machine becomes self-capable to identify what actually happening inside the video that it is recording and give out a readable and understandable output to the end user at the end of the day. The implementation should be in such a way that the machine can become self-capable to also identify about any discrepancies that has happened in the recording or any particular video and can infer it out to the end user.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: It would be a very useful tool for Content Moderation and Security Purposes

item.title: Image Classification
item.dc:creator: vaibhavwebdev23
item.content:encoded: Our project named Image Classification is based on Deep Learning and we have mainly focused on CNN (Convolution Neural Network) to train and test our project.Our main aim is to perform a comparative analysis using different image classification algorithms that can classify the image content based on designed parameters. For example, if there is an image that shows buildings, the output will be a tag classifying the image as building. Apart from this, our aim is to automate the process as much as we can and even optimize the predictions to reduce the number of false positives or false negatives.
item.excerpt:encoded: Humans are very good at categorizing scenes based on the semantic representation and object affinity, but we know very little about the processing and encoding of natural scene categories in the human brain. The same cant be said about the machines, The problem arises when we are required to determine a suitable classification system, selection of training samples, image preprocessing, feature extraction, etc. Image classification is the process of predicting a specific class, or label, for something that is defined by a set of data points. Image classification is a subset of the classification problem.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Its accuracy is more than 90% which is a great thing.
